I"I<p>Traditionally, rigorous version control systems have been constrained to the domain of programming. However, eerily similar patterns exist in other fields. For instance, a platform where artists share sketches and templates enables creatives to build on each other work, all while providing credit and incentives by design. Version control systems might also <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/interpersonal-backlinks-incentivize-collaborative-knowledge-work">help in collaborative knowledge work</a>, although creating knowledge from scratch is particularly valuable.</p>
